CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 10, 1967, pg. 17, reads: "Uganda Table - This table was one of many that was used to represent an African country. A glance can show the group was enjoying themselves."
TitMainTitle: Men and women gathered around table, some wearing African style clothing, with signs on tables reading "Uganda" and "Bamako," and balloons reading "Pipers," in the Flying Carpet for Alpha Kappa Alpha "Ajoyo"
